  <summary>4/17/2002--Introduced.
Small Business Expensing Improvement Act of 2002 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code with respect to the expensing of depreciable business assets (section 179) to: (1) increase the maximum amount which may be expensed to $40,000 (eliminating the current phase-in of annual increases) and the phase-out threshold to $325,000; and (2) make certain computer software and property used for lodging eligible for section 179 expensing.</summary>
